bib.title: Mass and energy distributions in the spontaneousfission of some heavy isotopes

free_txt: OG.
Two back-to-back phosphorus-disused guard-ring-
type silicon semiconductor counters.
Transcurium isotopes were produced by long-time
irradiation of curium isotopes with neutrons. The
elements were separated on ion-exchange columns. The
isolated and purified isotopes were electrodeposited
on approximately 5-mu-in.-thick Ni foils.
No information on sources of uncertainties.
